channel.title: The movie quote game
channel.description:
[COLOR='PaleGreen']Post a movie quote and others guess the movie, and then post their own movie quote. Example:
user1: [quote] "Listen, and understand. That terminator is out there. It can't be bargained with. It can't be reasoned with. It doesn't feel pity, or remorse, or fear. And it absolutely will not stop, ever, until you are dead." [/quote] user2: [quote]
[quote] "Listen, and understand. That terminator is out there. It can't be bargained with. It can't be reasoned with. It doesn't feel pity, or remorse, or fear. And it absolutely will not stop, ever, until you are dead." [/quote] Terminator [/quote] Searching for the answer on the internet is cheating. Dont be a turd and figure the answer on your own~!
[COLOR='DarkOrange']CatzEyes93: Original post here:
So, frequently my mind works in mysterious ways. There are many times where something will happen and my mind immediately connects it to a quote from a movie even if I don't remember what movie it comes from.
So, to waste some time before the mod is released, I propose the Movie Quote Game. You write a line from a movie and someone tries to guess it (try not to use the Internet for information) then post their own line.
Try to keep it to more mainstream movies. If you pick some foreign film that only three people have seen, no one will be able to guess it. You can use more obscure quotes from the movie, but I'd like to keep it to mainstream movies. So, I'll begin:
"Your mother is a fraggin' aardvark!"

item.title: The movie quote game
item.dc:creator: danielsangeo
item.description:
I love that scene in Willy Wonka and the Chocolate Factory. Each child got a “test” to see if they would be selfish or not. Augustus with the Everything’s Edible room, Violet with the gum chewing, Veruca with the Golden Geese, and Mike with the television camera technology. They all failed their tests. Charlie’s test, however, was being legally oppressed. His grandfather failed, but Charlie passed. It’s the best scene in the movie, IMHO, though somewhat difficult to watch.

Here’s an easy one:

“Almyra Gulch, just because you own half the county doesn’t mean you have the power to run the rest of us. For 23 years, I’ve been dying to tell you what I thought of you, but now, well… being a Christian woman, I can’t say it!”

Read full topic
